Xerox Corp said it has added asystem that can handle more than 3,000 calls per hour and storeup to 526 hours of messages to its Voice Message Exchangeproduct line.    Available with 12 to 64 ports, the new System V is designedto serve 800 to 10,000 users, the company said. It iscompatible with the company's entire voice message exchangeline, it added.    Xerox said the system may be rented annually, with anoption to purchase, starting at 4,700 dlrs per month, orpurchased for 123,000 dlrs. Reuter&#3;